## Core Logic (Already Built / In Progress)

### Baseline Modeling
- Aggregate raw RHR samples to daily mean
- Compute 30-day rolling mean as personal baseline
- Compute daily deviation = actual - baseline

### Drift Detection
- Look at last 14-day window
- Compute mean deviation + linear slope over that window
- Flag if mean deviation > threshold (currently ~3 bpm for RHR) and slope is positive

### What's Been Validated
- Real data shows a travel-induced spike of +10–14 bpm on Feb 13–14 (vacation)
- Baseline correctly captures slow seasonal drift (Nov–Jan elevation, then recovery)
- 3 missing days handled via NaN (pandas rolling handles naturally)

