## AI Insight Layer (Planned)
When drift is detected, pass a structured summary to Claude API:
- Signal name + current value
- Baseline value
- Deviation magnitude + direction
- Slope over recent window
- Any known context (travel, activity — eventually)

Claude generates a short, plain-English health insight:
- What changed
- Likely contributors
- What to do about it
- Tone: calm, informative, not alarmist

**Never pass raw data arrays to the AI.** Pre-compute the stats, pass clean structured summaries.

---

## What NOT to Do
- Don't add diagnosis language ("you may have X condition")
- Don't alert for single-day spikes — require sustained drift (multiple days)
- Don't use public health datasets — this is built on real personal data
- Don't add sleep analysis yet — no sleep data in current dataset
- Don't build mobile app yet — web first
- Don't add auth/multi-user yet — single user for MVP
